>
  <p>Joint injections are a way to provide targeted anti-inflammatory or healing properties to injured joints. This technique can preserve comfort and function longterm, while sparing the body from the systemic effects of long-term medication or pain that can lead to greater complications.</p>

  <p>Regenerative medicine often works with, or uses, the body to heal itself. These modalities often include components derived from the body, like platelet rich plasma, to create a medicine specific to your pet.</p>

  <p>Our doctors bring extensive experience from equine medicine, where joint injections and regenerative therapies have long been trusted tools for maintaining comfort and mobility. Drawing on this background, we thoughtfully adapt these proven approaches for our small animal patients, selecting from a range of injectable and regenerative options to create a plan that best supports your pet's unique needs and lifestyle. <a href="/acupuncture-pain-management-germantown-md/#Therapeutic_Laser">Therapeutic laser</a> is another form of regenerative medicine that Aspire uses to help patients with a multitude of conditions.</p>
